      },
      "formSubmission": {
        "visibleInput": "readonly text input for display only",
        "hiddenInput": "input[type='hidden'] with name attribute for form submission",
        "valueFormat": "Raw ISO format (YYYY-MM-DD, HH:mm, etc.) stored in hidden input",
        "description": "Visible input shows formatted value, hidden input stores raw value for forms"
      }
    },
    "implementationNotes": [
      "Initialization runs immediately on script load AND on astro:page-load for SPA navigation",
      "Double initialization prevented by checking data-init attribute before setting up handlers",
      "Input field is readonly - users cannot type directly, must use picker",
      "Icon button and input field both trigger same togglePicker function",
      "CRITICAL: stopPropagation() prevents race condition with PickerPopup's outside click handler",
      "Only one picker can be open at a time - opening one closes all others",
      "Popup ID is constructed as `${inputId}-popup` where inputId is the date input's id",
      "Picker component ID is constructed as `${inputId}-picker`",
      "formatDisplayValue function is duplicated in both server-side (Astro) and client-side (script) code",
      "Client-side formatDisplayValue uses hardcoded 'en-US' locale, but server-side uses locale prop",
      "Component listens for different custom events based on input type (date-select, time-select, etc.)",
      "Selection events automatically close the popup after updating values",
      "Hidden input always has same name as visible input for form submission",
      "Disabled state prevents both input and icon button interactions",
      "Icon button has tabindex=-1 when disabled to remove from tab order",
      "Picker popup positioning is handled entirely by PickerPopup component CSS",
      "Component supports 5 input types: date, time, datetime-local, month, week",
      "Each type renders different picker component (DatePicker, TimePicker, etc.)",
      "Value formatting differs significantly between types - see valueFormatting coordination section"
